{
  "genre": "jazz",
  "mode": "focus",
  "mixStrategy": "This arrangement is a classic jazz combo optimized for focus/flow state. FREQUENCY SEPARATION: Bass (acoustic upright) anchors 20-300Hz with walking quarter notes in MIDI 28-48 range, providing harmonic foundation. Chords (warm pad) fill 300Hz-2kHz with sustained 7th/9th voicings in MIDI 48-70 range, creating a warm harmonic bed that habituates quickly. Melody (acoustic piano) occupies 1-8kHz in MIDI 60-79 range with gentle arpeggiated lines and chromatic passing tones \u2014 the most prominent voice but kept at moderate velocity (50-70) for focus mode. Drums provide rhythmic skeleton across the spectrum with ride cymbal (presence), brush snare (high-mid), and soft kick (sub-bass), all at low velocity for subliminal pulse. RHYTHMIC INTERLOCK: Bass and kick lock on beat 1; ride plays a steady swing pattern; piano melody breathes in the spaces between ride hits, creating gentle forward motion without demanding attention. HARMONIC UNITY: All tracks follow the same chord progression \u2014 Cm7 (ii7) \u2192 F7 (V7) \u2192 Bbmaj7 (Imaj7) \u2192 Bbmaj7, then Dm7 (iii7) \u2192 Gm7 (vi7) \u2192 Cm7 (ii7) \u2192 F7 (V7), repeating. Chord changes happen every 2 beats (1.6s) or every bar (3.2s) depending on section. ENERGY ARC: Starts gently (0.4) with bass and pad only, melody enters at segment 2 (0.6), builds to 0.7 through the middle with fuller voicings and slightly busier melody, then tapers to 0.5 in the final segment for a gentle fade. The overall effect is a warm, predictable jazz wash that supports concentration \u2014 interesting enough to mask distractions but steady enough to habituate within 90 seconds.",
